# Modern CSS Techniques for Better UX

CSS has evolved tremendously, offering powerful features that can create stunning user experiences without JavaScript.

## CSS Grid and Flexbox

These layout systems provide unprecedented control over page layouts:

```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
  gap: 2rem;
}
```

## CSS Custom Properties

Variables in CSS make theming and maintenance easier:

```css
:root {
  --primary-color: #3b82f6;
  --secondary-color: #8b5cf6;
}

.button {
  background: var(--primary-color);
}
```

## Advanced Animations

- **CSS Transitions**: Smooth property changes
- **Keyframe Animations**: Complex, multi-step animations
- **Transform Functions**: 2D and 3D transformations

## Container Queries

Responsive design based on container size rather than viewport:

```css
@container (min-width: 400px) {
  .card {
    display: flex;
  }
}
```

These modern CSS features enable developers to create more engaging and responsive user interfaces.
